    @facw Sorta, I do have quite a few concert videos you can&#39;t stream.. but yeah I stream like no other like most
  @jminer Google kills everything half decent and it feels more and more like they&#39;re pimping my data. What were your thoughts on using an iphone coming from android? What drove you back?
  @benjrblant The biggest one was notifications and how you can interact with them. I like the linear and historic fashion of how android notifications work that allow me to interact with them without ever opening that specific app. Things like the mark as read on a text/delete an email and such I can do without opening an app or even unlocking my phone is great. I won&#39;t use a samsung phone either because they make managing and using notifications difficult too.
 Other things that pushed me back is the inability to properly arrange home screen icons. Want to put one at the bottom of the screen where you use it more but don&#39;t have enough items pinned to fill the screen? No such luck, top down - no other options for you!
 Also the inability to put widgets anywhere other than in a dedicated screen to the left of home (this one may be fixed in 15?)
    @benjrblant Google isn&#39;t a company, it&#39;s a bunch of fiefdoms of teams supporting apps. Everyone wants to work on the new hotness, so old apps eventually fall to the wayside and get shut down.
 It sucks and I wish that is something they&#39;d change. I loved Google play and cancelled my subscription because Youtube music is hot garbage.
